commit.message:
Merge pull request #24 from felgru/gcc-7-fixes

fix compilation with GCC-7

explicitly mark fallthrough case

This prevents another error that got introduced with the more thorough
diagnostics in GCC-7.

fix format truncation error with GCC-7

GCC-7 introduced new warnings and errors. Among them is a new warning
for possible truncations in the output of snprintf. Since we are only
interested in the return value of snprintf and do not use the string
written by it we can also replace the buffer with a NULL pointer.
This makes it explicit that we do not want to write a string and
silences the GCC-7 error.

See also the examples in
http://en.cppreference.com/w/c/io/fprintf
Fixes #23, shows help if no filename argument is supplied

Merge pull request #20 from NonerKao/master

New feature: add "cancel" option when exiting

New feature: add "cancel" option when exiting

Almost all other editors ask a user to confirm(y)/ignore(n) the
modification, or cancel(c) the exit and continue the editing,
which IMHO, is a general function for editors.

Merge branch 'master' of https://github.com/nilcons/hexcurse into nilcons-master

PR submitted by @nilcons resolves https://bugs.debian.org/cgi-bin/bugreport.cgi?bug=545711

Fix manpage

The manpage was issuing warnings, see for yourself with:
  man --warnings -l man/hexcurse.1 >/dev/null

The removal of the .SP lines doesn't change the formatting, it seems.

Do not ignore singals

This fixes multiple issues:
  - hexcurse was running 100% CPU when the terminal window got closed,
    and the HUP signal was not handled, see
    https://bugs.debian.org/cgi-bin/bugreport.cgi?bug=545711;
  - hexcurse was not exiting for SIGTERM;
  - it was not possible to put hexcurse into the background with SIGTSTP.
